# API Route Conventions

## Keep routes thin

API routes delegate to `src/lib/`. No business logic or DB queries inline in the route handler.

```ts
// ❌ BAD
export async function GET() {
  const { data } = await supabase.from("scenes").select("*");
  return Response.json(data);
}

// ✅ GOOD
import { getScenes } from "@/lib/supabase";
export async function GET() {
  const scenes = await getScenes();
  return Response.json(scenes);
}
```

## Admin routes

All routes under `src/app/api/admin/` must verify the Supabase Auth session before proceeding:

```ts
const { data: { session } } = await supabase.auth.getSession();
if (!session) return new Response("Unauthorized", { status: 401 });
```

## R2 uploads

File uploads go to R2 via presigned URL — never stream binary through a Vercel function. The upload flow is:

1. Client requests a presigned URL from `POST /api/admin/upload`
2. Client uploads directly to R2 using the presigned URL
3. On success, client calls `POST /api/admin/scenes` to save metadata to Supabase

## R2 URL shape

```
scenes/{scene-id}/video.mp4
scenes/{scene-id}/audio.mp3
textures/rain.mp3
textures/fire-crackle.mp3
```
